('business:4-6-working-with-suppliers:match:3425165a', 'business', 'business:4-6-working-with-suppliers', '4.6 Working with Suppliers', 'match', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "Which definition matches the key term “Customer Service (B2B)”?", "options": ["Selecting suppliers who operate responsibly — paying fair wages, protecting workers, and using sustainable materials.", "A system where materials or parts are delivered exactly when needed for production, minimising storage costs.", "A party that supplies goods and/or services to another business.", "The service a supplier provides to business customers to handle problems, faults, and enquiries."]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 3, "explain": "“Customer Service (B2B)” means: The service a supplier provides to business customers to handle problems, faults, and enquiries."}'::jsonb),
('business:4-6-working-with-suppliers:match:71456d9d', 'business', 'business:4-6-working-with-suppliers', '4.6 Working with Suppliers', 'match', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "Which definition matches the key term “Rainforest Alliance Certification”?", "options": ["Choosing suppliers — evaluating who can supply the goods, at what price, and with what level of quality.", "Selecting suppliers who operate responsibly — paying fair wages, protecting workers, and using sustainable materials.", "A system where materials or parts are delivered exactly when needed for production, minimising storage costs.", "A certification awarded to suppliers who meet ethical and environmental standards for sustainable production."]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 3, "explain": "“Rainforest Alliance Certification” means: A certification awarded to suppliers who meet ethical and environmental standards for sustainable production."}'::jsonb),
('business:5-1-role-of-finance-function:exam:92ae0b85', 'business', 'business:5-1-role-of-finance-function', '5.1 Role of Finance Function', 'exam', 'mcq', 1, '{"num": "Q1", "question": "Which task is most likely to be part of Sam''s job role? [1 mark]", "options": ["Phoning garages to negotiate vehicle servicing at reduced prices", "Posting discount codes on social media for pre-booked journeys", "Producing spreadsheets analysing quantitative market research data", "Providing cost data to help decide when to purchase new vehicles"], "caseStudy": "Sam is a finance assistant for a national taxi firm.", "hint": "Think about what a finance assistant specifically does — they deal with financial data, not advertising, procurement negotiation, or market research.", "starter": "The correct answer is D because..."}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 3, "markScheme": "<div class=\"marks-section\"><h5>Answer: D — Providing cost data to help decide when to purchase new vehicles</h5><p><strong>Why D is correct:</strong> Providing cost data to inform a purchasing decision is a core finance function — it involves producing and analysing financial information to support business decision-making.</p><p><strong>Why the other options are wrong:</strong></p><ul><li><strong>A — Phoning garages to negotiate vehicle servicing:</strong> This is a procurement or operations task, not a finance function. Finance does not negotiate external service contracts.</li><li><strong>B — Posting discount codes on social media:</strong> This is a marketing or sales activity. The finance team does not manage social media or promotional campaigns.</li><li><strong>C — Producing spreadsheets analysing market research data:</strong> Analysing market research is a marketing function. Finance may use spreadsheets, but for financial data (costs, revenues, forecasts) — not market research.</li></ul></div>", "modelAnswer": "D — Providing cost data to help decide when to purchase new vehicles."}'::jsonb),
('business:5-1-role-of-finance-function:exam:0ebd5e54', 'business', 'business:5-1-role-of-finance-function', '5.1 Role of Finance Function', 'exam', 'mcq', 1, '{"num": "Q3", "question": "Which business function is responsible for supporting business planning by anticipating periods of cash shortages? [1 mark]", "options": ["Finance", "Logistics", "Procurement", "Sales"], "hint": "Which department produces cash-flow forecasts — the financial plans that predict when money might run low?", "starter": "The correct answer is A because..."}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "markScheme": "<div class=\"marks-section\"><h5>Answer: A — Finance</h5><p><strong>Why A is correct:</strong> The finance function produces cash-flow forecasts that predict future inflows and outflows of money. This allows the business to identify in advance any periods where it may face a cash shortage, and arrange additional finance if needed.</p><p><strong>Why the other options are wrong:</strong></p><ul><li><strong>B — Logistics:</strong> Logistics manages the movement and delivery of goods. It does not produce financial forecasts or manage cash.</li><li><strong>C — Procurement:</strong> Procurement is responsible for sourcing and buying supplies. It interacts with finance in terms of budgets but does not itself anticipate cash shortages.</li><li><strong>D — Sales:</strong> Sales generates revenue by selling goods/services but does not manage or forecast the cash position of the business as a whole.</li></ul></div>", "modelAnswer": "A — Finance."}'::jsonb),
('business:5-1-role-of-finance-function:exam:7f0fc500', 'business', 'business:5-1-role-of-finance-function', '5.1 Role of Finance Function', 'exam', 'mcq', 1, '{"num": "Q4", "question": "Which of the following tasks is NOT a finance function? [1 mark]", "options": ["Advertising price reductions", "Applying for a bank loan", "Calculating break-even", "Measuring profit and loss"], "hint": "Think about which task involves communicating with customers rather than managing money and financial data.", "starter": "The correct answer is A because..."}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "markScheme": "<div class=\"marks-section\"><h5>Answer: A — Advertising price reductions</h5><p><strong>Why A is correct:</strong> Advertising is a marketing function. The finance department may set the advertising budget, but the actual creation and placement of adverts belongs to the marketing team.</p><p><strong>Why the other options are wrong:</strong></p><ul><li><strong>B — Applying for a bank loan:</strong> This is a finance function — sourcing external finance is one of the key roles of the finance department.</li><li><strong>C — Calculating break-even:</strong> Break-even analysis is a core finance function, telling the business how many units must be sold to cover all costs.</li><li><strong>D — Measuring profit and loss:</strong> Calculating and reporting profit and loss is a fundamental finance function, providing critical information for decision-making.</li></ul></div>", "modelAnswer": "A — Advertising price reductions."}'::jsonb),
('business:5-1-role-of-finance-function:exam:49ab0076', 'business', 'business:5-1-role-of-finance-function', '5.1 Role of Finance Function', 'exam', 'mcq', 1, '{"num": "Q5", "question": "Which functional area is responsible for providing information about a firm''s revenue? [1 mark]", "options": ["Finance", "Logistics", "Marketing", "Production"], "hint": "Revenue is financial data — which department tracks, calculates and reports on financial data?", "starter": "The correct answer is A because..."}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "markScheme": "<div class=\"marks-section\"><h5>Answer: A — Finance</h5><p><strong>Why A is correct:</strong> The finance function records and provides information about revenue — the money received from selling goods and services. Even though marketing activities generate sales, it is the finance function that measures and reports on the resulting revenue figures.</p><p><strong>Why the other options are wrong:</strong></p><ul><li><strong>B — Logistics:</strong> Logistics manages the movement and delivery of goods, not financial data.</li><li><strong>C — Marketing:</strong> Marketing creates campaigns that drive sales, but it does not formally track and report revenue — that is a finance responsibility.</li><li><strong>D — Production:</strong> Production focuses on making goods efficiently. It deals with output and costs, not revenue data.</li></ul></div>", "modelAnswer": "A — Finance."}'::jsonb),
('business:5-1-role-of-finance-function:exam:a3dd21b1', 'business', 'business:5-1-role-of-finance-function', '5.1 Role of Finance Function', 'exam', 'mcq', 1, '{"num": "Q6", "question": "Which one of the following is an example of how the finance function can support business activity? [1 mark]", "options": ["Analysing primary market research results", "Predicting revenues and costs", "Reviewing the quality of the products made by the firm", "Selecting staff for a business expansion"], "hint": "The finance function deals with financial data — revenues, costs, profits, forecasts. Which option involves financial data?", "starter": "The correct answer is B because..."}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 1, "markScheme": "<div class=\"marks-section\"><h5>Answer: B — Predicting revenues and costs</h5><p><strong>Why B is correct:</strong> Predicting (forecasting) revenues and costs is a core finance function. These forecasts support business planning by helping managers understand the financial implications of their decisions.</p><p><strong>Why the other options are wrong:</strong></p><ul><li><strong>A — Analysing primary market research results:</strong> Market research analysis is a marketing function. Finance does not collect or analyse customer feedback or survey data.</li><li><strong>C — Reviewing product quality:</strong> Quality control is an operations function. Finance does not inspect physical products.</li><li><strong>D — Selecting staff for a business expansion:</strong> Recruitment and selection is a human resources (HR) function, not a finance function.</li></ul></div>", "modelAnswer": "B — Predicting revenues and costs."}'::jsonb),
('business:5-1-role-of-finance-function:exam:f8e4670c', 'business', 'business:5-1-role-of-finance-function', '5.1 Role of Finance Function', 'exam', 'mcq', 1, '{"num": "Q7", "question": "Which one of the following tasks would be done by Taj? [1 mark]", "options": ["Creating educational resources", "Keeping the school website up to date", "Producing reports on the school''s GCSE results", "Providing financial data on school energy usage"], "caseStudy": "Taj is a finance assistant. He works in a secondary school.", "hint": "Taj works in finance — his role involves financial data. Which option involves financial/cost data rather than education, IT, or academic reporting?", "starter": "The correct answer is D because..."}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 3, "markScheme": "<div class=\"marks-section\"><h5>Answer: D — Providing financial data on school energy usage</h5><p><strong>Why D is correct:</strong> Tracking and reporting on costs — including energy costs — is a finance function. Providing this data helps management understand expenditure and make cost-saving decisions. This applies in any organisation, including a school.</p><p><strong>Why the other options are wrong:</strong></p><ul><li><strong>A — Creating educational resources:</strong> This is a teaching/curriculum responsibility, not a finance role.</li><li><strong>B — Keeping the school website up to date:</strong> This is an IT or marketing/communications role, not a finance role.</li><li><strong>C — Producing reports on GCSE results:</strong> Academic performance reporting is the responsibility of senior leadership or data managers, not the finance department.</li></ul></div>", "modelAnswer": "D — Providing financial data on school energy usage."}'::jsonb),
('business:5-1-role-of-finance-function:mcq:733029cd', 'business', 'business:5-1-role-of-finance-function', '5.1 Role of Finance Function', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "Sam is a finance assistant for a national taxi firm. Which task is most likely to be part of Sam''s job role?", "options": ["Phoning garages to negotiate vehicle servicing at reduced prices", "Posting discount codes on social media for pre-booked journeys", "Producing spreadsheets analysing quantitative market research data", "Providing cost data to help decide when to purchase new vehicles"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 3, "explain": "Correct answer: Providing cost data to help decide when to purchase new vehicles is a finance function — it involves analysing financial information to support a business decision. A is procurement/operations, B is marketing, and C is market research, not finance."}'::jsonb),
('business:5-1-role-of-finance-function:mcq:171a1e60', 'business', 'business:5-1-role-of-finance-function', '5.1 Role of Finance Function', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "Which business function is responsible for supporting business planning by anticipating periods of cash shortages?", "options": ["Finance", "Logistics", "Procurement", "Sales"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "Correct answer: The finance function produces cash-flow forecasts, which identify future periods when the business may have more outflows than inflows — allowing it to plan ahead and arrange additional funding if needed."}'::jsonb),
('business:5-1-role-of-finance-function:mcq:05bbf38c', 'business', 'business:5-1-role-of-finance-function', '5.1 Role of Finance Function', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "Which of the following tasks is NOT a finance function?", "options": ["Advertising price reductions", "Applying for a bank loan", "Calculating break-even", "Measuring profit and loss"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "Correct answer: Advertising price reductions is a marketing activity, not a finance function. Applying for a bank loan (sourcing finance), calculating break-even, and measuring profit and loss are all core finance department responsibilities."}'::jsonb),
('business:5-1-role-of-finance-function:mcq:fc9c4242', 'business', 'business:5-1-role-of-finance-function', '5.1 Role of Finance Function', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "Which functional area is responsible for providing information about a firm''s revenue?", "options": ["Finance", "Logistics", "Marketing", "Production"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "Correct answer: The finance function tracks and reports on revenue — the money received from selling goods and services. Marketing generates sales but it is finance that records and analyses the resulting revenue figures."}'::jsonb),
('business:5-1-role-of-finance-function:mcq:7f92fd1d', 'business', 'business:5-1-role-of-finance-function', '5.1 Role of Finance Function', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "Which one of the following is an example of how the finance function can support business activity?", "options": ["Analysing primary market research results", "Predicting revenues and costs", "Reviewing the quality of the products made by the firm", "Selecting staff for a business expansion"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 1, "explain": "Correct answer: Predicting revenues and costs is a core finance function — it provides the financial forecasts other departments need to plan. A is market research, C is operations/quality control, and D is human resources."}'::jsonb),
('business:5-1-role-of-finance-function:mcq:950db9f9', 'business', 'business:5-1-role-of-finance-function', '5.1 Role of Finance Function', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "Taj is a finance assistant working in a secondary school. Which one of the following tasks would be done by Taj?", "options": ["Creating educational resources", "Keeping the school website up to date", "Producing reports on the school''s GCSE results", "Providing financial data on school energy usage"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 3, "explain": "Correct answer: Providing financial data on energy usage is a finance task — it involves tracking costs for the school. A is teaching/curriculum, B is IT/marketing, and C is academic reporting, none of which are finance roles."}'::jsonb),
('business:5-1-role-of-finance-function:mcq:6404211d', 'business', 'business:5-1-role-of-finance-function', '5.1 Role of Finance Function', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "Which of the following is a role of the finance function?", "options": ["Advertise for temporary Christmas staff", "Decide on the style of a new television advert", "Monitor the costs and revenues of a business", "Make sure that the quality of goods made is of the highest standard"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 2, "explain": "Correct answer: Monitoring costs and revenues is a core finance function. Advertising for staff is HR, deciding on adverts is marketing, and quality control is an operations function."}'::jsonb),
('business:5-1-role-of-finance-function:mcq:ed7cbf2d', 'business', 'business:5-1-role-of-finance-function', '5.1 Role of Finance Function', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "Which of the following statements is FALSE?", "options": ["Business growth may be limited by problems of raising finance", "Finance is needed to pay for the start-up costs of a business", "Marketing costs are always paid out of revenue the business raises so finance is not needed", "A business may need to change its legal form to raise finances"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 2, "explain": "Correct answer: This is false — a new business or one launching a major campaign may need to source finance BEFORE it generates revenue. Marketing costs are not always self-funding, especially at start-up or during expansion."}'::jsonb),
('business:5-1-role-of-finance-function:mcq:f2281788', 'business', 'business:5-1-role-of-finance-function', '5.1 Role of Finance Function', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "A business that makes clothes decides to increase production. Which of the following is NOT likely to happen?", "options": ["Expenditures measured on the cash flow forecast will increase", "The firm may need to raise finance to expand the production facilities", "The total cost of production will increase", "The firm will spend less money on raw materials"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 3, "explain": "Correct answer: Increasing production means the firm will need MORE raw materials, not less. All other options are logical consequences of increasing production — higher expenditure, possible need for new finance, and higher total costs."}'::jsonb),
('business:5-1-role-of-finance-function:mcq:d1722d55', 'business', 'business:5-1-role-of-finance-function', '5.1 Role of Finance Function', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "The finance function of a business will NOT usually be involved in decisions about:", "options": ["Whether a business should introduce environmentally friendly practices", "Whether to switch production to goods aimed at a different market", "The appointment of a new apprentice in production", "How to proceed for a successful expansion of the business"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 2, "explain": "Correct answer: Appointing an apprentice is a human resources (HR) decision, not a finance function. The finance team would be involved in environmental decisions (extra costs), switching markets (revenue impact), and expansion planning (sourcing finance)."}'::jsonb)
